video_link: 
#### text ####
text: That evening, we went for a walk. I had recently gone on a plant identification walk, so Dad and I enjoyed trying to ID all the trees and some of the underbrush plants we saw. I was excited to find BC's native blackberry plant, the Trailing Blackberry. (I didn't get many photos because I was getting eaten alive by mosquitoes)
